caption: Mojito is very terrible , I dont think that bartender know how to make the drink probably , and the food price is too high for the quality . Taste of food not really authentic it s too fusion . Anyway we tips for the service but so disappointed with the food and drinks. Staffs is ok , they help us but food need to improve .

I want to preface this review with the fact that I'm a Laotian American from New York and that I've eaten a LOT of Lao food as someone who's grown up with it. So I was extremely excited to hear that a Laotian restaurant was opening up, so …

Intimate and cozy, currently with outdoor seating, the food is always delicous.  One of our favorite places to eat out downtown Greensboro.  Robert is the most creative bartender I've ever met - cocktails are outstanding!

Great experience! Quick seating and service. The chicken satay is a nice lite appetizer. The peanut butter sauce went great on everything. The other sauce was great for cleansing the palette. The wings came breaded with a Sriracha mayo on …
The food was delicious! A little spicier than I was anticipating, but I asked for spicy, so I got it!
The flavors are alot, but staff is knowledgeable and will help you navigate for the culinary lack of savvy. A damn fine smoked Tom Collins.  For real

We went here on a bit of a whim and we like supporting local businesses. I can honestly say we enjoyed our evening! Rob was our server and bartender. All of his recommendations were spot on! I started with a Paper Moon to drink...delicious …
Delicious food, great cocktails and wonderful people! Our favorite place!
The food was so savory. Will surely make a return trip. This place has many good reviews for a reason.

This is one of those rare instances in which Trip Advisor under serves raters such as myself by only allowing five stars. I don't live in Greensboro, but come to visit family. Lao was recommended by them. Just wonderful. We had the Sakoo …
Food was delicious. We ordered several dishes to share and they were all fantastic. Service was on point.

It's  different  from other Asian cuisine which ccj h is a welcome change. Expect nuts, rich seasonings, spice, overpowering  sauteed veggies  - all beautifully  unified. Robert is a great bartender. If you do not drink alcohol, ask him to make you a mocktail, he will whip you up something good.

The Money Bag fried Crispy wonton with cream cheese & imitation crab were really good. A little on the small size but the taste is delicious especially if you love cream cheese. The Kua Khao with chicken and fried rice, Fried with egg, …
The food here was excellent. Tries a lunch special chicken soup and some vegetable spring rolls. Service was great and food was flavorful and delicious.
Service was great, food was even better. Sticky rice, duck options, very flexible with menu variations. Great experience

Awesome food for downtown asian hot spot. Super fresh ingredients and you can ask for traditional style for a taste of the real thing! Surprisingly great bar and although our group came in for lunch I can wait to update our dinner experience.

They do a good job of showcasing the popular traditional dishes of Laos. Everything I have eaten here has been pretty close to the authentic thing. Definitely a good restaurant to try out the unique foods of Laos.

Awesome! Wish I had tried it sooner. The papaya salad reminded me of what I had in Thailand. The flavors in the Pun and Mee Kati were fantastic. I would have liked a little more heat in the Mee Kati but was sharing it with my wife who was happy with it. It is a nice little place that I'll look forward to visiting again.
Amazing staff and food
Loved the Jade Elephant cocktail. So good and the food was delicious too! Lovely hidden gem we are so happy we found.
Great food, drinks & service

Another Fantastic lunch. This place is PERFECT for a wholesome, healthy meal and the flavors are just spectacular. My favorite is the Khao Poon (coconut curry noodle dish) with tofu. You can swap out meats or tofu on most dishes here and …
Good food and nice people working here
Amazing service and more than amazing food.
The food here is delicious! I've been here twice and definitely plan on coming back again.
Absolutely amazing food and service.
Loved the appetizers. Staff was nice to warn us about spiciness level.
Atmosphere is on point and the curry noodle soups are BANGIN!! Mee Kati for sure a fav // always get extra crispy garlic to put on everything. Drooool
Yum

Excellent curry, great service. Music sound system is not good (sounds like the speakers are in the ceiling, which is quite high), and the selection of streaming songs is intrusive rock or pop or metal, not conducive to fine dining.

I went to Lao on a Saturday, so they were only open for dinner. I ordered the kua mee without the egg and with tofu. The noodles were incredibly flavorful and tasty, and so was the tofu. Don't be fooled by how small the plate is; the portion size is actually quite large and will definitely leave you satisfied.

Absolutely amazing food, drinks, and service! This was my first time at Lao and my experience was truly fantastic. I hardly ever post about restaurants, but this is one that honestly deserves 5 stars.
Excellent service and very attentive! Good taste and presentation and great selection of the meat cuts in entrees.
Really good food here, with a very attentive staff.
New for us but good food. I'd go back for sure.
First date....great date!!!

An amazing experience! The food was flavorful and really good, definitely recommend the Lao sausage or the money bags as appetizers, they both were awesome. The bartenders Austin and Matt were the best!, super friendly, attentive and knowledgeable, Can’t wait to go back!
Lao.  The food, the location, and the drinks make this one of downtown!s best places to eat.  Service has been very attentive every time I have eaten there.
Incredible food just bursting with flavor. FRESH cilantro graced the top of my dish. Excellent cocktails. 10/10 A+
Really good food. The bartenders are more of a mixologist than anything. Very nice people. Highly recommend this place.

Delicious, spicy flavorful food.  Lived in Chicago,  NYC- this restaurant can hold a candle with the best of them.  Loved the tofu mee kati, a rich red curry with more nuanced herb notes compared to a standard thai red curry.  Lettuce …
Austin and Matt were absolutely delightful bringing life to an already amazing dinner. The duck was amazing and I will definitely be returning.
Fantastic food, great flavors. We've only been for lunch, but look forward to trying this place again for dinner.
Great atmosphere, great service and amazing food
Delicious.  Try Seen Lod and Laab
Delicious food in a great atmosphere. They now do takeout!
The atmosphere was clean, modern, and relaxing. It was modern twist & mix of Thai and vietnamese dishes. The cocktails were creatively made, but could of used a little more seasoning/flavor.
Slow service but waiter was very nice and attentive
Food never fails to amaze. Great service. Staff works as a team.
I hope this place is here to stay, their food is so fresh and delicious. Better than thai food in my opinion, much more kick and pizzaz!

The catfish pun was delicious as were the spicy tuna bites. The bartender made me a customized thai tea with a kick that hit the spot. We had quite a long wait until our food arrived but we will definitely be back. Relaxing atmosphere and friendly staff.

caption: Amazing food served here, puts pad thai to shame. Incredible quality at affordable prices. Spread the word!
Great food! Had the chicken laab and spring rolls. Delicious!
Great food and cocktails. My mouth is burning slightly after the pleasantly spicy meal. WARNING: mildly spicy for me is very spicy for some.
So happy Greensboro finally has a Laotian restaurant! Very pleased with our meal and drinks.
Totally Charmed. Staff has been helpful with some of the more unusual Foods. And the food quality has been beyond expectations.

This is my first time having Laosian food and this restaurant totally did not let me down. Every single dishes was very flavorful. This is much better than Chinese food. The ambiance of this place is small but definitely offer the BEST food …

With me living and working downtown I frequent Lao quite often. The food and service are amazing. It is obvious the food is made fresh daily with no shortcuts. So happy to have them as an option in the neighborhood.
Refreshing change for Greensboro, well done everyone.

This place is it! If you like Thai, Vietnamese, India, Malaysian then this place is for you. I feel like it's all those 4 wrapped in one. The drinks are just as fresh and unique as the food. The pompano is a must, with fresh cilantro cherry …
Food was incredible,  service and ambience matched.
Great food. Great ambience. Great service.
The food was okay but the prices were unacceptably high! the only thing that’d stop me coming here would be the prices of the food.

Nice to see this still new restaurant with a good crowd last night.  The food was very good although too spicy for one of our party.  Staff reacted well to his discomfort and replaced the offending papaya salad.   Lao will spice to your level of enjoyment.  The sticky rice and mango desert was excellent.

Awesome new place in downtown Greensboro, definitely check them out, everything we had was delicious. Crab wonton appetizer was delicious and presented in a way I had not encountered before. Loved the noodle dish recommended to us by the waiter. Amazing mango cocktail! Definitely go for date night.

I really like the curry. Spicier than other's I've had so be careful if you don't like the heat. The pompano was just OK. Lot's of good looking items on the menu so I will be back. And props to the King Colada cocktail.  Lot's of coconut milk and a dark rum floater!
Greensboro has been needing a place like this. Great drinks, great atmosphere, with unique and delicious food. Lao is already one of my favorite places in the Triad.

Great menu, large portions at reasonable prices. Somewhat delayed service for food, but I’ll chalk that up to the place being new and them working to figure out the service flow. Pretty traditional cocktail menu with some novel takes on the classics. Really enjoyed my meal, would definitely come back!
Great food and atmosphere!
So far so good. The spicy papaya salad and the Lao pho was both amazing. Full of flavor. The bartender know his stuff as well. Will be back soon.

Possibly the worst service I've ever had. The food was phoned in,for instance the "lao sausage" tasted premade. The cocktail menu was every boring drink imaginable plus basil or ginger.  I was hoping for bida manda and was deeply disappointed.  Why bother?
Very flavorful food and great staff.
Went here for lunch with my wife and we both really enjoyed our meals. It was crazy busy so I took a star for service. It was worth the wait and we’ll be back.

We loved our meal here and the excellent service.  Glad to have something so nice in the former location of Crafted.  I got the chicken laab salad which had the perfect combination of spices and fresh vegetables.  My dad got the red curry …
Absolutely outstanding!!! Beautifully designed interior and the food was incredibly delicious.  So excited to have this new restaurant in Greensboro! I will be back many, many times.
